curlPython <pre><code>curl -X POST https://bookcorners.org/api/v1/auth/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "username": "janedoe",
    "email": "jane@example.com",
    "password": "s3cure!Pass"
  }'
</code></pre> <pre><code>import requests

resp = requests.post(
    "https://bookcorners.org/api/v1/auth/register",
    json={
        "username": "janedoe",
        "email": "jane@example.com",
        "password": "s3cure!Pass",
    },
)
tokens = resp.json()
</code></pre> <p>Response (<code>201 Created</code>):</p> <pre><code>{
  "access": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...",
  "refresh": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs..."
}
</code></pre> <p>Save both tokens. The <code>access</code> token is short-lived; the <code>refresh</code> token lets you obtain new access tokens without re-authenticating.</p>
